<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Tue 15 Dec 2009
Source: Panapress, Panafrican News Agency (PANA) report [in Portuguese,
trans., edited]
<http://www.panapress.com/freenewspor.asp?code=por008294&dte=15/12/2009>


Outbreak of measles reported in Zimbabwe
----------------------------------------
Health authorities in Zimbabwe reported on Monday [14 Dec 2009] an outbreak
of measles in various provinces of the country. Most cases involved members
of registered religious groups that refuse conventional medical treatments.

To contain this disease, the authorities have launched a national
immunization campaign against measles and other preventable diseases for
children under five years of age.

